  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nplease note that this is an issue tracker reserved for bug reports and feature requests.\r\n\r\nFor general questions please use the gitter channel or the Ethereum stack exchange at https://ethereum.stackexchange.com.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth 1.8.12`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nI use eth_newPendingTransactionFilter and the command should give me result very quickly.\r\ncurl --connect-timeout 10 --data-binary '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":\"curltext\",\"method\":\"eth_newPendingTransactionFilter\",\"params\":[]}' -H 'content-type:application/json;' http://172.16.254.113:8545/\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":\"curltext\",\"result\":\"0xb54a0f559435683098edfd035b0ea94e\"}\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nSometime, the command will hangs up and no reply. Then next curl commands will hang up too. I have to restart geth to release them. Otherwise, other method such as eth_blockNumber works fine when the eth_newPendingTransactionFilter hangs up.\r\ncurl -v -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -X POST -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":\"curltext\",\"method\":\"eth_blockNumber\"}' http://172.16.254.113:62003/\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nCan not reproduce with certain method. The case will appear at random time. I have collect some pprof logs but no clues to trouble shooting.\r\nhttp://172.16.254.113:6060/debug/pprof/profile\r\nhttp://172.16.254.113:6060/debug/pprof/goroutine\r\nhttp://172.16.254.113:6060/debug/pprof/heap\r\nhttp://172.16.254.113:6060/debug/pprof/threadcreate\r\nhttp://172.16.254.113:6060/debug/pprof/block\r\nhttp://172.16.254.113:6060/debug/pprof/mutex\r\n\r\n[pprof.tar-1.gz](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/files/2216699/pprof.tar-1.gz)\r\n[pprof.tar-2.gz](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/files/2216700/pprof.tar-2.gz)\r\n[pprof.tar-3.gz](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/files/2216701/pprof.tar-3.gz)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n[backtrace]\r\n````\r\n",
